  "text": "In addition to the analysis of these cell-line DNA mixtures, the ability to detect rare HLA sequences present in mixtures was demonstrated in the analysis of blood from a SCIDS patient (Table 4) . In this patient, the rare nontransmitted maternal allele could be detected along with the inherited maternal and paternal alleles. The potential to analyze chimeric mixtures may have important applications in clinical research [CITATION_1] .",
